Mountain Realm - Shadowlorn [ Full Album.title: Mountain Realm - Shadowlorn [ Full Album ] - Dungeon Synth
Mountain Realm - Shadowlorn [ Full Album.desc:
Retro Dungeon Synth Ambience for roleplaying from Mountain Realm
👉Bandcamp: https://cryocrypt.bandcamp.com/album/...
👉Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/album/39imSZ...

Mountain Realm (of projects Atrium Carceri/Za Frûmi) presents his 3rd album on Cryo Crypt. A mist filled ancient nordic folk tale fantasy that starts in the Whitebark Forest

As the last wisps of sunlight fade, the Whitebark forest succumbs to the Shadowlorn's dark grasp. The ancient trees, once verdant and proud, now stand as skeletal sentinels, their leaves withered and grey. The elves, attuned to the forest's subtle rhythms, feel the Shadowlorn's presence like an open wound, its influence seeping into the land like a chill that cannot be shaken.

In this desperate hour, whispers of a forgotten remedy begin to circulate, spoken in hushed tones around flickering campfires and in the shadowy recesses of the forest. They speak of the Ruby of the Ancients, said to hold the only hope of stemming the Shadowlorn's relentless tide. Hidden deep within the ruins of the Fallen Kingdom, the ruby's existence is a fragile thread, the last lifeline for a world on the brink of collapse.

As the stars begin their slow wheeling in the night sky, the wind stirs, carrying the whispers of the past on its breath. The Fallen Kingdom's crumbling spires, once proud and tall, now stand as a haunting testament to the transience of power. Yet, it is within these ancient stones that the ruby is said to lie, waiting for one brave enough to claim it. The darkness closes in, but the promise of the ruby remains, a desperate gamble against the Shadowlorn's crushing darkness.

Gather your gear, shoulder your pack, and prepare to venture into the shadows of the Fallen Kingdom, where the whispers of the past await, and the promise of the ruby beckons.

Recommended for fans of Nordic Folk, retro CRPGs, and PnP RPGs.

WORK MUSIC - 1 Hour of Ultimate Work Music for Deep Focus and Efficiency

Welcome to Deep Chill Music's "WORK MUSIC - 1 Hour of Ultimate Work Music for Deep Focus and Efficiency"! This specially curated playlist is designed to help you achieve deep focus and maximize efficiency during your work sessions. Whether you're working on complex projects, managing tasks, or engaging in creative activities, this music provides the perfect ambiance to boost your productivity.

Immerse yourself in soothing melodies and ambient sounds that create an ideal work environment. Let our carefully selected tracks guide you into a state of deep concentration, reducing distractions and enhancing your workflow.

WORK MUSIC - 1 Hour of Ultimate Work Music for Deep Focus and Efficiency
WORK MUSIC - 1 Hour of Ultimate Work Music for Deep Focus and Efficiency
WORK MUSIC - 1 Hour of Ultimate Work Music for Deep Focus and Efficiency

Tips for Optimal Productivity:

Time Blocking: Allocate specific time slots for focused work on individual tasks.
Regular Breaks: Take short breaks to rejuvenate your mind and maintain high energy levels.
Organized Workspace: Keep your workspace tidy to minimize distractions and enhance focus.
Headphones: Use headphones to eliminate external noise and immerse yourself in the music.
Microdosing Caffeine: Consume small amounts of caffeine throughout the day for sustained alertness.
If you find this video helpful, please like, comment, and subscribe to our channel for more productivity-boosting music mixes. 🙏 Join our community to connect with like-minded individuals and share your productivity tips. ❤️

Indonesia is comprised of diverse cultures and languages. From Sabang to Merauke, each region has its own unique characteristics. The diversity of languages, dances, music, and traditions come together in a harmonious unity.

Presented by 9 talents of hololive Indonesia, this is the medley of folk songs in Indonesia that you have been waiting for!

#holoIDJiwaKarya

\u2600\ufe0f Chillhop Essentials \u00b7.desc:
Essentials Summer 2022 picks up where we left off inside the Chillville metropolis. Here, our Raccoon mascot - alongside Milkshake the Bear and Mango the Toucan - settles into a new apartment, explores a new city, and surrenders to the seemingly endless Summer. The temperatures are climbing and the heat is inescapable. So grab a pool umbrella, find your favorite sunglasses, and turn up the boombox.

At 24 songs with 35 musicians, Essentials Summer 2022 marks the 26th seasonal compilation since beginning back in 2016. Lofi and lively, jazzy and upbeat, press play and take to the beach.

Cafe in the Morning🌻Take a time to work/relax/study with Lofi Music🎧~ Lofi Coffee☕[ Chill Hip Hop ]

The sun peeks through the window of a quaint cafe, casting a warm glow on the wooden tables and comfy armchairs. A gentle hum fills the air, a mix of soft conversation and the rhythmic hiss of the espresso machine. Open your laptop, unfurl your notebook, or simply lose yourself in a good book.  Lofi music, with its calming melodies and soft beats, washes over you, creating a focused and yet relaxed atmosphere, perfect for a productive morning.

"Lofi Coffee" is a cozy corner where the aroma of freshly brewed coffee mingles with the soothing melodies of lo-fi music. Step into a world where every sip is accompanied by the gentle hum of vinyl crackles and the rhythmic beats of relaxation. With its laid-back atmosphere and warm ambiance, "Lofi Coffee" invites you to unwind, slow down, and savor the simple pleasures of life, one cup at a time. Whether you're starting your day or seeking a moment of respite, let the tranquil vibes of this enchanting space envelop you in comfort and contentment.

~ Lofi Coffee ☕ ~

How To Write A Twist Villain - Wreck it.title: How To Write A Twist Villain - Wreck it Ralph
How To Write A Twist Villain - Wreck it.desc: In this video essay, we explore how Disney crafted the perfect twist villain in Wreck-It Ralph. From the seemingly harmless King Candy to the shocking reveal of his true identity as Turbo, we’ll break down the subtle clues and brilliant storytelling that made this twist so impactful. We’ll analyze how Disney subverted expectations, turning a fun and colorful world into a dark tale of obsession and betrayal. Through clever foreshadowing, character development, and a seamless blend of humor and suspense, Wreck-It Ralph delivers one of Disney’s most memorable and surprising villains. Join us as we unpack the genius behind this twist and why it stands out in Disney’s animated legacy.

Bolt: The Masterpiece That Never Got A S.title: Bolt: The Masterpiece That Never Got A Sequel
Bolt: The Masterpiece That Never Got A S.desc:
Get ready to dive into the world of Bolt, one of Disney's most underrated gems! In this video, we explore why Bolt is a true masterpiece that captured the hearts of audiences but never received the sequel it deserved.

Released in 2008, Bolt tells the story of a super-powered dog who believes he has real powers, only to discover that his life as a TV star isn’t what it seems. With its unique premise, heartwarming characters, and stunning animation, Bolt stands out as a shining example of Disney's storytelling magic. 

A big step for Disney at the time, after several questionable movies. But why didn’t Bolt get a sequel? We'll dive into the reasons behind this surprising decision and explore how the movie's legacy lives on despite the lack of a follow-up. Could there still be hope for Bolt 2? Let's speculate on what a sequel might look like and why fans continue to rally for more adventures with our favorite super-dog.

Whether you’re a longtime Bolt fan or discovering this movie for the first time, this video is a must-watch! Don’t forget to like, subscribe, and hit the bell icon for more Disney deep dives and animated movie magic!

The RISE, FALL, and RISE again of Deadpo.title: The RISE, FALL, and RISE again of Deadpool
The RISE, FALL, and RISE again of Deadpo.desc:
Deadpool is one of the most popular superheroes in the world, but it wasn't always that way. He was poorly adapted in X-Men Origins: Wolverine, no studio wanted him to have his own movie, and Ryan Reynolds had to fight for years to redeem Wade Wilson in live action. In this video, we explain how Deadpool became Marvel's most popular antihero, how he was almost forgotten, and how he made a comeback to save the MCU and change the superhero genre forever.

Plants vs. Zombies is a video game franchise developed by PopCap Games, a subsidiary of Electronic Arts. The series follows the affiliates of David "Crazy Dave" Blazing as they use his plants to defend against a zombie invasion, led by Dr. Edgar George Zomboss.

This Plants Vs. Zombies Movie showcases the Pea Shooter Game (豌豆射手) where you can combine bootleg PVZ plants like peashooter and chomper to create fusion plants like Fire Peashooter and Cob Cannon. This ripoff game has so many combinations of plants as well as a knockoff Zomboss that it makes for a great Plants Vs. Zombies Movie!

 Again, if you want more videos like this then go ahead and subscribe to my channel. 😚

Samurai Champloo (Japanese: サムライチャンプルー, Hepburn: Samurai Chanpurū) A young woman named Fuu is working as a waitress in a tea shop when she is abused by a band of samurai. She is saved by a mysterious rogue named Mugen and a young rōnin named Jin. Mugen attacks Jin after he proves to be a worthy opponent. The pair begin fighting one another and inadvertently cause the death of Shibui Tomonoshina, the magistrate's son. For this crime, they are to be executed. With help from Fuu, they are able to escape execution. In return, Fuu asks them to travel with her to find "the samurai who smells of sunflowers".

Immerse yourself in this serene urban nightscape paired with mellow lo-fi beats. Perfect for relaxation, study, or just taking a moment to unwind after a long day. This video combines visually soothing animations of a city at night with calming lofi music that will transport you to a place of tranquility. Let the subtle rhythms and soft melodies be your companion through this nocturnal journey. The cityscape, with its starry sky and ambient lights, creates a perfect backdrop for the soothing music. Whether you're looking to relax, focus, or simply enjoy some peaceful moments, this video is your go-to. Don't forget to hit like, share, and subscribe for more relaxing music content! Stay tuned for more updates and let us know in the comments how this music helps you. Your support means a lot to us!

Russian Doomer Music || Russian Post-Pun.title: Russian Doomer Music || Russian Post-Punk Collection || Царствие тебе панельное mixtape
Russian Doomer Music || Russian Post-Pun.desc:
Ночь. Ход времени застыл. Выходишь на балкон, достаешь огонёк, неторопливо потягиваешь сижку. Дым сигареты сливается с дымом заводских труб. На душе тепло. Приятная пустая тишина...
Снова залипаешь на эти дома, никак не изменившиеся за четверть века. Они все так же мрачно стоят и устало молчат. Потом задумываешься, сколько же жизней в этих ульях с панельными сотами, что все они будут бесславно закончены; прожиты как под копирку и ничем не запомнятся.
А затем вспоминаешь детство, в котором все казалось особенным, даже ожидание каждодневной прогулки с друзьями будоражило сознание. Вспоминаешь про постоянные теплые посиделки с бесчисленными родственниками, которых ты лет 10 уже не видел. Поражаешься тому, как раньше всё было предельно ясно. А теперь все вопросы остаются риторическими. Все непонятно. Нет белого и черного, лишь множество градиентов серого. Жизнь пролетает, а ты все так же ждёшь, ждёшь чего-то светлого, но тут заканчивается сижка... пора возвращаться с балкона...

Если понравился плейлист и очень ждешь следующий...

Songs that are like V\u00d8J, Narvent -.desc:
#memoryreboot #synthwave 
Main song is: VØJ, Narvent - Memory Reboot.

𝐒𝐮𝐛𝐬𝐜𝐫𝐢𝐛𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝟐!
Psst! More here :p  Patreon:   / lvert1go  

I needed to make a playlist that consist of songs that are like and matches the vibe of memory reboot while also fitting in the edits of blade runner 2049.

Each piece that was played, have deeply touched me as a person, guiding me to a soundscape that resonates with the combined essence in the song. I am not sure what it is, but the emotions that the song shows indirectly, has made me speechless. The creative brilliance of both the track and the film, deeply touched me.

I am a guy that enjoys phonk music, blasting my ears with many kinds of upbeats, but memory reboot changed and altered my gears in my music taste. 

In conclusion, I was so touched by the masterpiece that I am so compelled to make a playlist matching the vibe. I've included the sped up version because it is what it is, loss for words. So many versions of the song and yet... it works. Ultimately, ending off with memory reboot slowed version to show my appreciation.

So thank you and credits to ‪@NarventMusic‬  and VØJ for your masterpiece.

Also big credit to creators such as ‪@FrankJavCee‬ ‪@TheMotion‬  Home and ‪@PASTELGHOSTx‬ .

This Is the Calculus They Won't Teach Yo.title: This Is the Calculus They Won't Teach You
This Is the Calculus They Won't Teach Yo.desc:
"Infinity is mind numbingly weird. How is it even legal to use it in calculus?"

"After sitting through two years of AP Calculus, I still feel like I don’t know anything about it."

"What do you mean that historically, integrals came before derivatives? Seriously, what’s the deal with calculus?"

There is an inspiring story hidden behind the formulas and word problems of single-variable calculus–a story that should be told in every introductory calculus course, but usually isn’t. Regardless of if you’ve taken a few calculus courses before or are just beginning your study of calculus, this video aims to give a taste of the insights that can be gained from learning about the history and philosophy behind the key ideas of this field of math… brought to you by a dog and some rough animations!

This video was part of #SoME2, a math video making contest created by ‪@3blue1brown‬ in the summer of 2022.

=====================================================================

Chapters:
0:00 Chapter 1: Infinity
1:49 Chapter 2: The history of calculus (is actually really interesting I promise)
2:19 Chapter 2.1: Ancient Greek philosophers hated infinity but still did integration
7:43 Chapter 2.2: Algebra was actually kind of revolutionary
11:14 Chapter 2.3: I now pronounce you derivative and integral. You may kiss the bride!
19:53 Chapter 2.4: Yeah that’s cool and all but isn’t infinity like, evil or something
24:14 Chapter 3: Reflections: What if they teach calculus like this?

=====================================================================

LINK TO FURTHER READING AND SOURCES: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1K...

Thank you very much to Dr. David Bressoud for letting me interview him!



If you have any questions, thoughts, recommendations or you notice any mistakes, please do share!

=====================================================================

CORRECTIONS LIST (periodically being updated):

3 : 47 I start a description of Archimedes' circle proof here, but I want to note that the one I present is a modified version of it; it does contain a few "hand-wavy" mistakes near the end and may still be difficult to follow; that's on me. My goal with showing this proof wasn't to give a proper explanation of it, but to give a taste of what I thought is the spirit of rigorous reasoning. If you would like to see something that is closer to Archimedes' argument, there's a link in the further reading you can check out--or you could also just google "Archimedes circle proof".

8 : 45 I made a typo... Viete lived from 1540-1603, not 1540-1693

14 : 35 This is embarrassing. Kepler's 2nd law is true because angular momentum is constant, not because velocity is constant. Whoops!

A lot of comments have brought up Indian contributions to calculus that I left out, particularly the Kerala School and Madhava of Sangamagrama, where the first instances of derivation came about. A few reasons for why I missed this in my research could be because attributing the beginnings of calculus with Indian mathematicians seems like a relatively new historical narrative, and many sources in English likely have a bit of Eurocentric bias. Regardless, this goes to show how the narrative I shared does have its flaws, and similarly to the misleading impression of calculus I criticized modern introductory courses of spreading, this narrative is not the whole picture. If you have any sources you'd like me to add to the further reading, please let me know!

I may have suggested that Euler discovered the number e, but he did not--some attribute it to Napier, and many others before Euler used it. On that note, I probably misleadingly attributed a lot of other ideas I brought up to one or a few people, when they are much more nuanced; so take the briefly brought up associations in this video with a grain of salt. This video is intended to share a broad narrative instead of establish definitive history of calculus. Hopefully this can just act as an intro to the subject!

In this video me, TapL, PeteZahHutt, and 4 others teamed up in MineDraft Twitch Rivals and got 2nd place! ---------------------------------------------------------------------

The Woods
This song is about escaping the mundane and going out into nature to find peace. It was one of the first songs we ever wrote together and it was actually the song that really started everything for us. We recorded it in a friend's garage. At first, we only put it on Soundcloud because we thought it wasn’t good enough for iTunes or Spotify. We both had normal jobs and always thought music would just be a hobby. Then this song started going viral on Soundcloud and we have been making music ever since. 

Coastline
We both grew up on the east coast of Australia. However, we actually wrote this song while we were living in Canada. We spent some time living in Toronto, very far from any coastline, and while we were there we were reminiscing on road trips up and down the east coast of Australia and this song was born. We recorded it in a little studio in Montreal, and the recording engineer must have misheard us when we told him the song name because when we looked at the computer he had titled the song ‘Toastland’. 

Evermore
About 4 years ago, Matt’s sister approached him and told him that she was struggling to find a song to walk down the aisle to on her wedding day. She asked if he could write a song for her. Of course, he said yes! So he wrote this song and performed it with his brother as she walked down the aisle. After the wedding, we both listened to the song and thought it was special. We worked on it together to try and shape it into something for Hollow Coves. The song sat with us for the next few years. 

Blessings
Blessing is a song of gratitude. It’s about recognizing the little blessings that life has to offer. If we don’t take a moment to acknowledge them; we can often miss them. Practicing gratitude is known to be good for mental health, yet anxiety and depression seem to be more and more prevalent in our generation. I think this generation is just too distracted to stop and take time to practice gratitude. We wanted to write this song to help people to realize that there are blessings all around if you just look up and take the time to think about how much we have to be grateful for. 

Lonely Nights
When we first wrote ‘Lonely Nights,’ we were on tour in Europe and missing home. We were reminiscing on times spent with friends and lamenting missing events. Now, given the events of the last year and a half, we can’t help but think that this is a feeling that so many people would have experienced, and may still be experiencing, through the COVID lockdowns and times of isolation. We hope this song can give people a sense of peace and hope for the future.

Hello
This song was actually based off one of the first songs Matt ever wrote back in school. He stumbled across the song again during COVID lockdowns and some new verses came to mind. After he finished writing it he uploaded an iPhone recording to Dropbox where we both share new ideas. It was only up on Dropbox for about 5 minutes and then he decided to delete it. Luckily I had received a notification that it had been uploaded and listened it in those few minutes and I messaged him straight away to tell him that I loved it. 

#hollowcoves #indie #aesthetic

How are Microchips Made? \ud83d\udda5\uf.title: How are Microchips Made? 🖥️🛠️ CPU Manufacturing Process Steps
How are Microchips Made? \ud83d\udda5\uf.desc:
Go to http://brilliant.org/BranchEducation/ for a 30-day free trial and expand your knowledge. Use this link to get a 20% discount on their annual premium membership.

Integrated Circuits, CPUs, GPUs, Systems on a Chip, Microcontroller Chips, and all the other different types of microchips are the brains of all the devices and technology that we use on a daily basis.  But have you ever wondered how these microchips are made?  Well, in this video, we're going to take a tour of a microchip fabrication plant or fab and walk you through the dozens of steps used to make a microchip.  Specifically, we focus on how CPUs are made.  CPU, GPU, and Smartphone Microchip manufacturing is a multi-trillion dollar industry, and each factory costs in the tens of billions of dollars.  This is an overview of all the processes used to make a microchip, as well as an overview of a microchip factory.  We're planning more videos on microchip manufacturing, such as a 3D animated factory tour.  

This is the MOST complicated video we've made by FAR!!  4 different animators have been working on this video non-stop for the past 5 months, for a total of 1300 hours of research, modeling, script writing, animating, editing, animating again, rendering, and then more editing.   Support us on Patreon is you want more videos like this one.

The Product Mindset Meets AI.title: The Product Mindset Meets AI
The Product Mindset Meets AI.desc:
Gen AI promises to completely transform our world, from how we work to how we live. But do the core first principles in product management and strategy change with this new technology? 


Join Matt as he digs into this question with Uday Kumar, Principal - Data and AI Product Management at Metashore. Uday shares his insights on maintaining core principles in product management while leveraging the new tools and technologies offered by generative AI. He emphasizes that while the fundamentals of understanding customer needs and solving problems remain unchanged, generative AI presents a new and compelling toolset. 


They also discuss the potential of generative AI to revolutionize sectors like healthcare, fintech, and education by making complex technological solutions more user-centric and effective and highlight the importance of 'falling in love with the problem'—spending significant time understanding the issue before looking at the tools available to solve it. The conversation also explores how organizations can start integrating generative AI into their operations. 


Key moments:

  •  Gen AI and product strategy
  •  Fundamentals of project management in the age of AI
  •  Challenges and opportunities with gen AI
  •  Implementing gen AI in organizations
  •  Data considerations and security in AI 
  •  Strategic implications of gen AI
  •  The future of AI Agents and project management
  •  How to get in touch with Uday 


Key links: 

  •  Metashore (https://metashore.com/) 
  •  Connect with Uday on LinkedIn (  / udaykumardc  )

Gen AI Innovation Workshop


Generative AI is revolutionizing industries, staying ahead means not just understanding its capabilities but actively leveraging them. This episode dives into Hatchworks' cutting-edge Generative AI Innovation Workshop, designed to equip businesses with the knowledge and tools needed for success in this transformative landscape.

Join us as we explore:
1. Introduction to Generative AI: An overview of how generative AI is reshaping industries and why it's critical for businesses to adapt.
2. Hatchworks' Innovation Workshop: A detailed look into our full-day immersive workshop focused on generative AI. Discover how we combine learning, hands-on ideation, and practical building activities to enhance your understanding and application of AI in your business.
3. Foundational Concepts: Insight into the key concepts of generative AI and how they apply to your specific domain, paving the way for innovative thinking and application.
4. Use Case Development: Learn how we guide participants through the process of identifying and developing real-world use cases tailored to their business and industry needs.
5. Custom GPT Creation: An exciting peek into how we build a custom GPT model based on defined use cases, offering a glimpse into the tailored solutions that can drive your business forward.

Whether you're looking to deepen your understanding of generative AI or seeking actionable ways to implement AI strategies in your business, this episode is a must-listen. Dive in with us at the Hatchworks Innovation Workshop and start unlocking the full potential of generative AI for your business.

The fire crackles rhythmically and whimsically as you rest your head against your heavy but snug travel cloak, you've had a long day and now it's time to relax.  You've eaten half a bowl of the best stew in these parts, and you've had some good strong ale, you feel fuzzy and warm to the toes.  Just then the glissando of a woodland harp reaches your ears from across the tavern - the music is about to begin!  As the soft melodies mingle with the sounds of the fire you feel waves of relaxation and restoration come over you.  You haven't felt this good in ages. 😌🎶

Our passion is to transport you to magical virtual realms to find a blissful escape from reality!  We open portals to spaces that calm the mind, soothe the senses, assist creativity and bring restoration to your spirit.  So if you're looking for a cozy and inspiring place to relax then welcome friend.  We bring you ancient rooms for studying, soothing sounds for sleep, peaceful white noise for meditation, crackling fire sounds, medieval harp music, deep relaxation vibes, Celtic ASMR and more.

Ethereal Harmony: J-Pop Piano and Soothi.title: Ethereal Harmony: J-Pop Piano and Soothing Synths
Ethereal Harmony: J-Pop Piano and Soothi.desc:
Enjoy the ethereal harmony of Japanese pop piano and soothing synth sounds. Our latest Lofi music video, "Ethereal Harmony: J-Pop Piano and Soothing Synths," features calming melodies perfect for creating a relaxing atmosphere. Whether you're studying, working, or simply unwinding, this video provides the ideal soundtrack.

The combination of J-Pop piano melodies and soothing synth sounds invites you into a world of tranquility. The gentle melodies and peaceful nighttime imagery offer a delightful relaxation experience.

🌙 Features:

Calming Piano Melodies: Smooth beats perfect for relaxation and concentration.
J-Pop Melodies: Tunes inspired by Japanese pop music.
Soothing Synth Sounds: Soft, relaxing sounds.
Beautiful Imagery: Tranquil night scenes.
Thank you for watching! Please like, comment, and subscribe for more serene music.

日本のポップピアノと心地よいシンセサウンドで、幻想的なハーモニーをお楽しみください。最新のLofi音楽動画「Ethereal Harmony: J-Pop Piano and Soothing Synths」では、リラックスした雰囲気を作り出す穏やかなメロディをお届けします。勉強や仕事、リラックスするために、この動画は完璧なサウンドトラックです。

J-Popのピアノメロディと心地よいシンセサウンドの組み合わせが、あなたを穏やかな世界へと誘います。柔らかなメロディと静かな夜の風景が、心地よいリラックスタイムを提供します。

🌙 特徴:

穏やかなピアノメロディ: リラックスと集中に最適な滑らかなビート。
J-Popメロディ: 日本のポップミュージックからインスパイアされたメロディ。
心地よいシンセサウンド: リラックスできる柔らかなサウンド。
美しい映像: 静かな夜の風景。
ご視聴ありがとうございます！ぜひ、いいね、コメント、そしてチャンネル登録をして、より多くの穏やかな音楽をお楽しみください。

Zelda & Jazz.title: Zelda & Jazz
Zelda & Jazz.desc:
Jazz piano, upright bass, and mellow percussion set the stage for the debut release of The Deku Trio. "Zelda & Jazz" is a 12 track tribute to The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time. Get the album ▸ https://vgm.fm/zeldajazz

The Deku Trio is a new project from Rob Araujo (Chillhop) and Chris Davidson (GameChops) that elevates video game covers through forward-leaning arrangements for jazz trio. 

Highlighting fan favorites like Song of Storms, Zelda’s Lullaby, and Great Fairy Fountain, The Deku Trio's coffeehouse-style reimaginings feature cozy ornamented piano arrangements, interesting reharmonizations, soulful basslines, and delicate drums and percussion. Music composed by Koji Kondo, with arrangements by Rob Araujo, and artwork and character designs by award-winning comic author Riana Dorsey.

Zelda & Jazz is out now on all online stores and streaming platforms! Support The Deku Trio and GameChops Unplugged by streaming, saving, and adding the tracks to your playlists.

This channel is the world reference for RPG audio on YouTube, with hundreds of top-quality ambiences and songs, five new creations per week and an incredibly active and friendly community. The team is composed of Michael Ghelfi and Filip Melvan. Michael makes the ambiences and some music, and Filip makes the music.
The ambiences are composed with world class AAA+ libraries or home-recorded sound effects.
We got tons of exclusive content on Patreon. Your help is welcome to help us keep doing this full time.

Welcome back adventurers!

This track is all about travelling in the wilderness and I wanted to mix different feeling you would get while adventuring in uncivilized lands through this musical piece.

INTERSTELLAR MUSIC mix during Sunset [HD.title: INTERSTELLAR MUSIC mix during Sunset [HD]. AMBIANT Music for working, playing or dreaming.
INTERSTELLAR MUSIC mix during Sunset [HD.desc:
One hour of interstellar mix, during a sunset (Stantonset actually). 
Includes titles from the movie "Interstellar" (soundtrack Hans Zimmer) and other musics of the same inspiration.
Big up to all these talented artists who would deserve more recognition. 
Shot from Port Tessler spacestation in orbit around planet Microtech (from Star Citizen space simulation game).

Musics with pipe-organ chords and synth layers that sometimes resonate quietly, sometimes epic. Relaxing Instrumental ambiant music conducive to dreams, introspection and relaxation.
This sunset reflecting through the clouds and atmosphere realistically modeled in Star Citizen, embellish the experience.

I love to work, create or play space games while listening to music on my TV screen, with an inspirational landscape. Just like this one ! 
I hope you like it ! Also, if any idea for next videos, let me know in the comments !

Big up to all these talented artists who would deserve more recognition.

The Key Equation Behind Probability.title: The Key Equation Behind Probability
The Key Equation Behind Probability.desc:
Get 4 months extra on a 2 year plan here: https://nordvpn.com/artemkirsanov. It’s risk free with Nord’s 30 day money-back guarantee! 

Socials:
X/Twitter: https://x.com/ArtemKRSV
Patreon:   / artemkirsanov  

My name is Artem, I'm a graduate student at NYU Center for Neural Science and researcher at Flatiron Institute (Center for Computational Neuroscience).

In this video, we explore the fundamental concepts that underlie probability theory and its applications in neuroscience and machine learning. We begin with the intuitive idea of surprise and its relation to probability, using real-world examples to illustrate these concepts.
From there, we move into more advanced topics:
1) Entropy – measuring the average surprise in a probability distribution.
2) Cross-entropy and the loss of information when approximating one distribution with another. 
3) Kullback-Leibler (KL) divergence and its role in quantifying the difference between two probability distributions.

OUTLINE:
00:00 Introduction
02:00 Sponsor: NordVPN
04:07 What is probability (Bayesian vs Frequentist)
06:42 Probability Distributions
10:17 Entropy as average surprisal
13:53 Cross-Entropy and Internal models
19:20 Kullback–Leibler (KL) divergence
20:46 Objective functions and Cross-Entropy minimization
24:22 Conclusion & Outro

Wavelets: a mathematical microscope.title: Wavelets: a mathematical microscope
Wavelets: a mathematical microscope.desc:
Wavelet transform is an invaluable tool in signal processing, which has applications in a variety of fields - from hydrodynamics to neuroscience. This revolutionary method allows us to uncover structures, which are present in the signal but are hidden behind the noise. The key feature of wavelet transform is that it performs function decomposition in both time and frequency domains. 

In this video we will see how to build a wavelet toolkit step by step and discuss important implications and prerequisites along the way.

This is my entry for Summer of Math Exposition 2022 ( #SoME2 ).
My name is Artem, I'm a computational neuroscience student and researcher at Moscow State University. 
Twitter: @artemkrsv



OUTLINE:
00:00 Introduction
01:55 Time and frequency domains
03:27 Fourier Transform
05:08 Limitations of Fourier
08:45 Wavelets - localized functions
10:34 Mathematical requirements for wavelets
12:17 Real Morlet wavelet 
13:02 Wavelet transform overview
14:08 Mother wavelet modifications
15:46 Computing local similarity
18:08 Dot product of functions?
21:07 Convolution
24:55 Complex numbers
27:56 Wavelet scalogram 
30:46 Uncertainty & Heisenberg boxes
33:16 Recap and conclusion
